  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Warehouse Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Receiving and Processing Shipments:</strong></p>\n<p>· Receive incoming shipments and verify their contents against purchase orders or packing slips.</p>\n<p>· Inspect shipments for damages or discrepancies and report any issues to the appropriate personnel.</p>\n<p>· Organize and properly store received inventory in designated locations within the warehouse.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Order Picking and Packing:</strong></p>\n<p>· Pick items from inventory based on order requirements using handheld scanners or picking lists.</p>\n<p>· Pack items securely for shipment, ensuring proper packaging materials and labelling are used.</p>\n<p>· Prepare orders for shipping, including generating shipping labels and coordinating with carriers for pickup.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Inventory Management:</strong></p>\n<p>· Assist in conducting regular inventory counts and reconciling discrepancies.</p>\n<p>· Maintain accurate records of inventory levels and locations using inventory management software or manual logs.</p>\n<p>· Monitor inventory levels of essential items and communicate reorder needs to the warehouse supervisor.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Warehouse Organization and Cleanliness:</strong></p>\n<p>· Keep the warehouse clean, organized, and free of safety hazards.</p>\n<p>· Arrange inventory and shelving systems for efficient storage and accessibility.</p>\n<p>· Dispose of packaging materials and other waste in accordance with company guidelines.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Equipment Operation and Maintenance:</strong></p>\n<p>· Operate warehouse equipment such as pallet jacks and hand trucks safely and efficiently.</p>\n<p>· Perform routine maintenance checks on warehouse equipment and report any malfunctions or issues to maintenance staff.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Compliance and Safety:</strong></p>\n<p>· Adhere to all company policies, procedures, and safety regulations.</p>\n<p>· Follow proper procedures for handling hazardous materials and maintaining a safe working environment.</p>\n<p>· Participate in training sessions related to safety protocols and warehouse procedures.</p>",
